Having mentioned the erect position, it is almost unnecessary to add, that it is altogether unnatural to these creatures; and that although we see their skeletons constantly distorted into human attitudes, one grand characteristic between them and us is the impossibility of their thigh-bone being brought, by fair means or by the action of their own muscles, into the same line as that of the spine.
